6.30	Reverend_and_the_Makers	Reverend and The Makers	Reverend and The Makers are an indie pop band based in Sheffield, England and signed to Wall of Sound. The band is fronted by Jon McClure, nicknamed "The Reverend". The band's debut album The State of Things (2007) has helped them gain success in Britain, as well as spawning UK Top 10 single "Heavyweight Champion of the World". The band released their second album, A French Kiss in the Chaos (2009) which led to the band being invited to support Oasis on their last ever tour, playing venues such as Wembley Stadium. The band's third studio album is set to be released in 2012 after a two year break from music, and will be entitled @Reverend_Makers, and will be released in May 2012.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/RevmakersSSW08.JPG/220px-RevmakersSSW08.JPG
